# RAG Document Q&A — Chat with your Documents

Upload a PDF and ask questions about it. Answers are generated **only from the
document's content**, streamed token-by-token, with **source citations** showing
exactly which passages the answer came from.

![Demo](docs/demo.gif)

## How it works

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  U[User] -->|upload PDF| C[React Client]
  U -->|ask question| C
  C -->|POST /upload| S[Express Server]
  C -->|POST /ask - SSE| S
  S -->|extract, chunk, embed| DB[(MongoDB Atlas
Vector Search)]
  S -->|semantic retrieval| DB
  S -->|context + question| G[Gemini API]
  G -->|streamed answer| S --> C
```

1. **Ingestion** — PDF text is extracted (unpdf), split into overlapping chunks,
   embedded with Gemini (`gemini-embedding-001`, 768 dims), and stored in
   MongoDB Atlas with a vector index.
2. **Retrieval** — the question is embedded with the same model and the most
   relevant chunks are found via `$vectorSearch`, filtered by document.
3. **Generation** — retrieved chunks are injected into the prompt; Gemini answers
   strictly from that context and cites the passages used. Off-document questions
   get "I couldn't find that in the document" instead of a hallucination.
4. **Streaming** — answers stream to the React UI over Server-Sent Events.

## Stack

Node.js · Express · React (Vite) · MongoDB Atlas Vector Search · Gemini API · unpdf

## Run locally

```bash
# server
cd server
npm install
# create server/.env with:
#   GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key
#   MONGODB_URI=your_atlas_uri
node server.js

# client (second terminal)
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
```

Requires a MongoDB Atlas cluster with a vector search index on `ragdb.docs`
(768 dimensions, cosine) plus a `docId` filter field.